metadata.name: M'Fing Dots #63
metadata.description:
[AIRDROP] - M'Fing Dots (not on a M'Fing Grid) is an AIRDROP for owners of "M'Fing Dots on a M'Fing Grid": https://www.fxhash.xyz/generative/17648

These are dots, but, well, not on a grid - about the simplest dots you could get.

When the project launches, 150 will be minted, and snapshot of owners from MFDOAMFG will be taken and these M'Fing dots will get airdropped.

s - To save an image
h - To toggle to high-rez

metadata.name: ανοχή #31
metadata.description:
ανοχή
Tolerance and difference transforming simple oscillations on beautiful vision.
Takes about 10 seconds to loading all layers.

No distocion rate 25%, ondulation = 0
Speed change under 5.5 rate 10%, movimento < 5.5

A Piece to be rarer it needs to be geometric and slower, so the ondulation is equal to 0, so for better visualization, slow movements being movement less than 5.5

Press 'S' to print in full screen view and full quality. 
NFT made with hydra.ojack

metadata.name: The Living Book #2 Moonrise #22
metadata.description:
I have been exploring the medium of print for years. Mixing etching, silk-screening, offset, photocopy, risography, drawing and painting to design and craft experimental art books.From the day digital, which had always fascinated me, took over my publishing practice, I always liked to create bridges between these two worlds.

The Living Books is part of this series of hybrid and experimental works where paper and digital resonate.

This issue #2 is made of 64 pages that will be minted by collectors. A book will eventually be printed and the pages will follow the mint order. Each page exists in a cover version (c) and a xerox version (x).

Controls :

• Click to dive into each frame.
• Press C to toggle cover mode.
• Press X to toggle xerox mode.
• Press 1, 2, 3, or 4 to make a capture and download a PNG with a resolution of x1, x2, x3 or x4.

———————

The Living Book #2 Moonrise by Ferdinand Dervieux, 2022
Made with Unity

metadata.name: Petri 1500 #137
metadata.description:
Petri 1500 is a celebration of reaching 1500 Twitter followers.
As I've grown as an artist what represents that growth but a petri dish, filled with life, finding a way. 

A sillybration of all things fx(hash) featuring some of my recognisable pallets and primatives
along with something new to me - noise and 'realistic' nature sketches. 
All mashed for pure fun.

L to download 1000x1000
S to download 4000x4000

metadata.name: Encapsulated #3
metadata.description:
Have you ever felt fear? Have you ever felt tired? Have you ever felt trapped and watched? The bars of the big cities are supposed to bring us protection, but in the end, we are encapsulated in this big prison.

This project was made thinking about that feeling of prison ourselves and will participate in the #fxhashturnsone event. 

Fully made with p5.js and p5.grain

metadata.name: Trading Art #12
metadata.description:
Visualize the price chart of major Forex pairs, BTC and ETH.

There are 5000 H1 candle data imported for each one, which means more than 50K H1 candles in total, with random background color, background patterns, and moving average period and style it provides good enough variations.

I start coding from first Covid quarantine by the Forex trading bots, first MQL4 then Python, and so on, in all of those experiences I have to play all the time with the OHLC data, which stands for Open, High, Low, and close price of a specific period, for example, one hour(H1).

Now I use them to make generative color paint for those people who are interested in Forex or Trading and spend a lot of time seeing these candles on the screen!

You can hold it in your wallet or print it and hang it on the wall.

Press “s” key to save in original size.

Made with p5.js
